achgebrauch in Zusammenhang stehen. Sie zeigt, dass Dialekte über diskursive Prozesse konstruiert und im Sprachgebrauch reproduziert werden und damit, wie Dialekte von Sprechern gemacht werden.  aThis empirical study examines the importance of dialect and dialect use in Switzerland. Based on interdisciplinary approaches, it explores the extent to which linguistic perception and assessment on the part of laypersons is connected to actual language use. It shows that dialects are constructed by means of discursive processes and reproduced in language use. In this way, it illuminates how speakers create dialects.  afunded by Schweizerischer Nationalfonds (SNF)  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aPhilology. Linguistics. 4aDialektologie. 4aDiskurslinguistik. 4aSoziolinguistik. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aDialectology.  adiscourse linguistics.  asociolinguistics.2 aSchweizerischer Nationalfonds (SNF)efunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2019z9783110606287oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831106602890 cprintz978311066022740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110660234zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110660234zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110660234.jpg  a978-3-11-069627-1 DG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1b2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb20